
---


@startuml
' Classes
class WebPortal {
  - version: String
  - url: String
}

class Building {
  - id: String
  - name: String
  - energyClass: String
  - address: String
  - yearOfConstruction: Integer
  - owner: User
  - entries: List<Entry>
  - images: List<Image>
  - profilePhoto: Image
}

class Entry {
  - name: String
  - isPublic: Boolean
  + addEntry(): void
  + updateEntry(): void
}

class TextualEntry {
  - content: String
}

class NumericEntry {
  - value: Float
  - unit: String
}

class Image {
  - fileName: String
}

class User {
  - username: String
  - email: String
  - password: String
  + register(): void
  + login(): void
  + createBuilding(): void
  + manageEntries(): void
  + commentOnBuilding(): void
}

class Administrator extends User {
  - idCardNumber: String
  + setupUserAccount(): void
  + deleteComment(): void
}

class Visitor {
  + searchBuildings(): void
}

' Associations
WebPortal "1" --> "0..*" Building
Building "1" --> "0..*" Entry
Building "1" --> "0..*" Image
Building "1" --> "1" Image : profilePhoto
Entry "1" --> "1" TextualEntry
Entry "1" --> "1" NumericEntry
User "1" --> "0..*" Building
User "1" --> "0..*" Comment

@enduml

---

### 📌 **Use Cases & Actors Mapping**

| Use Case                     | Actor        |
|-----------------------------|--------------|
| Register as a user          | Visitor      |
| Log in                      | User         |
| Create a building           | User         |
| Add an entry to a building  | User         |
| Manage entries              | User         |
| Comment on a building       | User         |
| Delete a comment            | Administrator|
| Search for buildings        | Visitor      |
| Setup user account          | Administrator|

---

### 🧩 **Generalization Relationships**

- `Administrator` is a special kind of `User`.
- `TextualEntry` and `NumericEntry` are both types of `Entry`.

---

### ✅ Notes:

- The `Entry` class is abstract, with two concrete subclasses (`TextualEntry`, `NumericEntry`) representing different types of data.
- `Image` is used for storing building images, and one image is designated as the profile photo.
- The `User` class has multiple responsibilities, including managing buildings and commenting.
- Administrators inherit from `User` but have additional capabilities like setting up users and deleting comments.

